			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2067194">
									

<p>Regarding the Maxwellians, I imagine that their gospels are translated into a wide variety of (programming) languages, but is there any particular language that is regarded as &quot;superior&quot; to the others, in terms either of piety or scholarly acumen? Sort of like how Latin was treated in the real world for a long time?</p>
<p>I only had a couple computer programming courses myself, but since Latin serves as a root language for many that came after it (hence Romance languages), I'd imagine the programming language equivalent might serve that role as well. With that in mind, it might be BASIC or C (or C+ perhaps), but again, I don't know as much about programming as I'd like to.</p>

